<paragraph pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 79" captionStartId="F79" captionText="Figure 79. Distribution of Conostegia fragrantissima." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96437" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">79</figureCitation>
). Known from south eastern Costa Rica and west Panama, 1200-1700 m elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="974195" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96437" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" start="Figure 79" startId="F79">
<paragraph pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Figure 79.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia fragrantissima" order="Myrtales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fragrantissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Conostegia fragrantissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<bibRefCitation author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Almeda, F" journalOrPublisher="Flora Mesoamericana" pageId="239" pageNumber="240" pagination="164 - 338" refId="B8" refString="Almeda, F, 2009. Melastomataceae. Flora Mesoamericana vol. 4: 164 - 338" title="Melastomataceae." volume="vol. 4" year="2009">Almeda (2009)</bibRefCitation>
synonimized 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia fragrantissima" order="Myrtales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fragrantissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Conostegia fragrantissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Despite the heterogeneity present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there was no stigma lobes in several living populations studied, or was there an evident style declination as is present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia fragrantissima" order="Myrtales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fragrantissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Conostegia fragrantissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. My observations contrast with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Schnell’s">Schnell's</normalizedToken>
because he stated most populations of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do present a lobed stigma and a declinate style. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
makes a good point in stating that collectors tend to overlook fragrance, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the most frequently collected species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia" order="Myrtales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Conostegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and none of the specimens studied cited floral fragrance. On the other hand, of the only six specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia fragrantissima" order="Myrtales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fragrantissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Conostegia fragrantissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, one describes evident fragrance (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Almeda et al. 6040</emphasis>
- CAS, MO, NY). The stigma lobes present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia fragrantissima" order="Myrtales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fragrantissima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Conostegia fragrantissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as the declinate style (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 78" captionStartId="F78" captionText="Figure 78. Conostegia fragrantissima. A Inflorescence B Close up of flowers at anthesis C Flowers bud with longitudinal section to the side D Pickled flower at anthesis E Style F Longitudinal section of the hypanthium G Stamen H Petal. Photos A-B of specimen vouchered F. Almeda 6040 (CAS) and taken by Frank Almeda C-H of specimen vouchered R. Kriebel and D. Solano 3174." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure78" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96436" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">78</figureCitation>
) also suggest a possible relationship to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia pittieri" order="Myrtales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pittieri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Conostegia pittieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Unfortunately this species was not included in the phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia" order="Myrtales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Conostegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and thus its close relatives remain unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
